                                        <comments>
                            <comment id="15107738" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 00:28:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I setup a branch on GitHub with the fix: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/tree/11037-2.2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/tree/11037-2.2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107739" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 00:29:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/tree/11037-2.2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/tree/11037-2.2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15107740" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 00:30:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m new to JIRA and contributing to Apache Cassandra, so if I did something wrong, please let me know.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15108688" author="carlyeks" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 15:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kf6nux&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kf6nux&quot;&gt;kf6nux&lt;/a&gt;: Thanks for the patch! Unfortunately, this won&apos;t work on OS X as &lt;tt&gt;readlink&lt;/tt&gt; does not take &lt;tt&gt;-f&lt;/tt&gt; as an option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the Cassandra JIRA, the &quot;Ready to Commit&quot; state is for when the reviewer has finished looking at the patch and determined that it is ready to be committed; the state this should have been in was &quot;Patch Available&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109146" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 18:54:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=carlyeks&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;carlyeks&quot;&gt;carlyeks&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the JIRA info and raising the Mac OS compatibility issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would be okay to have this script depend on perl?  Then we could resolve the cross platform compatibility and symlink issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something like:&lt;br/&gt;
python &quot;$(dirname $(perl -e &apos;use Cwd &quot;abs_path&quot;;print abs_path(shift)&apos; $0))/cqlsh.py&quot; $@&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109180" author="jmckenzie" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 19:03:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not a safe assumption that perl is going to be installed on a Windows environment, unfortunately.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109206" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 19:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=JoshuaMcKenzie&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;JoshuaMcKenzie&quot;&gt;JoshuaMcKenzie&lt;/a&gt; Wouldn&apos;t a windows environment be executing the cqlsh.bat file and not the cqlsh bash script?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109461" author="kf6nux" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 21:27:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Switched from readlink to perl for Mac OS compatibility. Github updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15109743" author="jmckenzie" created="Wed, 20 Jan 2016 23:41:03 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t a windows environment be executing the cqlsh.bat file and not the cqlsh bash script?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Absolutely. I misread your diff and thought you were changing cqlsh.py (which, in retrospect, would make no sense at all given the change you&apos;re talking about).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ignore me and carry on. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15110984" author="kf6nux" created="Thu, 21 Jan 2016 17:47:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch available on github: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/commit/1459703decacdf1582fbef5d6b88f039ca40662a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/commit/1459703decacdf1582fbef5d6b88f039ca40662a&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15111052" author="carlyeks" created="Thu, 21 Jan 2016 18:29:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since we are already requiring that users have python installed, we can do the same thing with that instead of requiring perl as well:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;python &quot;`python -c &quot;import os;print(os.path.dirname(os.path.realpath(&apos;$0&apos;)))&quot;`/cqlsh.py&quot; &quot;$@&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WDYT, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kf6nux&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kf6nux&quot;&gt;kf6nux&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15113187" author="kf6nux" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2016 21:59:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=carlyeks&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;carlyeks&quot;&gt;carlyeks&lt;/a&gt; That makes way more sense.  Thanks for that.  &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I updated my github repo and will update the JIRA thread.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15113190" author="kf6nux" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2016 22:00:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/commit/070c26898756e00b69ce233e3d32f54056c688b9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/kf6nux/cassandra/commit/070c26898756e00b69ce233e3d32f54056c688b9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15153081" author="carlyeks" created="Thu, 18 Feb 2016 21:06:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=kf6nux&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;kf6nux&quot;&gt;kf6nux&lt;/a&gt;. Committed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/cassandra.git/?p=cassandra.git;a=commit;h=4985fcc86f8b28887c5ed41e538354ab07cb6f70&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;4985fcc&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
